Below is a large checklist (150+ test cases) you can use for Broken Authentication testing when building your automated tool. The structure is inspired by testing practices from OWASP and the OWASP Foundation Testing Guide.

I grouped them so your tool can run modules.

1. Login Form Security Tests (20 tests) 🔐

Login with empty username

Login with empty password

Login with both fields empty

Login with very long username (5000 chars)

Login with very long password (5000 chars)

Login with SQL injection payload

Login with XSS payload

Login using unicode characters

Login with leading spaces in username

Login with trailing spaces in username

Login with uppercase vs lowercase username

Login using email instead of username

Login with invalid email format

Login with multiple login attempts quickly

Login with different user agents

Login from multiple IP addresses simultaneously

Login using disabled account

Login using deleted account

Login using expired account

Login with session already authenticated

